We found squashed some bugs that snuck out in the last update. We re very sorry about these happy singing! Fixed feedback from microphone when recording Fixed issue where some videos were failing to upload

UPDATE: If you are having trouble posting videos dismissing the app in the background and re starting it should fix future uploads. We re very sorry! This will be fully fixed soon. In the last update: Tweaked color and font sizes to suit eyes of all ages. We even tested this version for color blindness. Fixed recording details screen to show the full album art. Album art is the window to the soul of the music. We get it you want to see the full album art we do too. Fixed volume control and video sliders to be more responsive. It was way too skinny before. Fixed glitches when swiping on comments to reply delete or flag. Improved connection speed to the messaging server. Preview recording details directly from the message center. As always email support smule.com to let us know what you think of the update or anything that s on your mind. We are listening!

Hello Sing!ers Spring is here and so is a fresh new look and feel for the Sing! app. You ll find lots of improvements big and small throughout the app. New font face Proxima Nova which improves legibility and readability on all devices. Unified the style and color palette of all the icons and buttons. We like colors too but there were way too many different colored buttons before causing confusion even with ourselves! Fixed the banners that appear on the songbook for iPhone 6 and bigger devices so it can actually fit in the bigger screen. Video indicator is now vertical strips instead of horizontal for the people that still know what a film reel looks like. Yah we re with you. No more swiping left to love blindly without listening. Nuff said. Previously listens were being undercounted so that s now fixed and you may see your listen counts go up. That s a good thing! Cleaned up lots of crufty code you don t want to know too much about this except that it s always a good thing and makes our engineers happy to clean up code. This update is more than a fresh new look. Read more about it at http: blog.smule.com We also want to make sure the app works even better for you than before. So please let us know at support smule.com if there is anything amiss. We are always listening and working on further improvements.

v4.5.9: Resolved an issue with microphone permissions. Reminder: You must accept mic permissions on your device in order to sing! If you accidentally declined mic permissions you ll need to manually re enable it in iOS settings. Contact support smule.com if you need help with this. v4.5.7: Fixed a bug involving video uploads v4.5.5: This is a big one folks! USABILITY Improved Find Friends Reduced Open Mic minimum length from 1:00 to 0:30 Various tweaks to Feed layout PERFORMANCE Reduced recording lag on older devices Reduced audio sync issues on older devices Increased smoothness of Group Video filmstrip BUGS CRASHES Fixed bug where pitchlines disappeared when singing certain duets Fixed bug where final score 0 when singing certain duets Fixed bugs related to Facebook accounts Fixed bug where Open Mic previews froze the app Fixed bugs affecting saving a performance with headphones plugged in

NEW FEED: Keep up with your friends or find someone new to sing with. VIDEO FX: When creating a video performance swipe across the screen to enable sweet visual effects like Sepia Comic or Vintage! NEW SINGING SCREEN: Crisp modern recording interface that s easier to use. iOS8 only IMPROVED REWIND: It s easier to rewind your performance and erase mistakes as you sing! Hello Sing!ers! We heard you loud and clear. Thank you! In this update: You can see who joined the performance in notifications. You can see the album art of the performance in notifications. Overall improvements to make the text more readable in notifications. Squashed silly bug where you can not customize the album art of Open Mic songs. Customize away! Fixed audio gain issue between performance and upload if you rewind. Audio is always tricky thanks everyone for all your patience and help. Please email support smule.com if you are still seeing volume mismatch issues. As always we are working on bettering the app experience. We are listening send your feedback to support smule.com And don t forget all the goodies from the last update: Join video duets! Click to filter for video only in your song open calls lists. So la ti do you want a Sing! update ! Duets are now even easier to follow with new icons and colors to help you remember which part is yours. Hello again talented Sing!ers! Today s update is all about you: specifically your feedback! We made several changes to the main menu so that it will be easier to understand what the options all do. Some examples: Recent Open Calls is now Sing with Others My Feed is now Notifications Explore is now Hot Recordings In addition to making the app easier to navigate we also made a TON of audio improvements all over the app plus a fancy new animation at the top of the songbook! Finally we wanted to give you a heads up that some BIG thing are coming soon! Got any guesses Head to our Smule Facebook page and let us know!
Hello again Sing!ers! This release is just a tiny bug fix to make sure you can sing to your heart s content. Enjoy!

Reporting in from the What s New Text Writing Lab. Today s updates are all about making it easier for you to find Cool Stuff. We also heard your feedback fixed bugs and improved your audio experience! First notifications are improved! They now show on the left menu when you have something new in your feed or an invite to check out. Search is also always available for you now on the right side of the songbook better for you to find the exact song you want to sing and get into the groove. And last but not least we added a Play button on all album art so that previewing songs and performances is faster and better than ever before! Have fun Sing!ers!

Today s update brings you more fun and personalized ways to sing with others! First we ve added a new Recommended for You playlist with suggestions based on what you want to hear and sing. We ve also expanded Invite Friends options: folks can join your open calls via Facebook text Twitter and email now! SmulePick a themed playlist hand picked by our very own Community Manager Zhen will refresh every week. If you d like a chance to be featured be sure to use the hash tag! And last but not least a friendly and super helpful PSA: don t forget to clear your cache sometimes! To clear your cache go to the Settings page. Clearing your cache will save space will make your app experience quicker and smoother. Enjoy the update!

Hello Sing!ers! Smule What s New Writing Team here to report in on what s going on in the Sing! Making Stuff Awesome Lab. There s a brand new Explore Screen for you to enjoy including Undiscovered Talent. Be the first to be found or find the first if that s your thing! We ve also added new audio effects called Super Studio and Super Pop complete with sliders to customize the effect. It s fantastic. Can t wait to hear you guys with it! And last but not least a couple requests directly from the community: you can now sort the Songbook by Artist and follow Sing!ers easily after you join them in a recording. Keep that feedback coming! And with that... we re going back into the lab. Imagine lots of beakers just with musical notes.

April Showers bring May flowers... And also a Sing! update. First things first we have a snazzy new icon. The community voted and this one reigned victorious! Isn t it purdy We ve added a Recent Opens screen to make duet browsing more fun and easy. Now you can check out what Open Calls have just been created and use them as digital muses while deciding your next performance. The team s been working under the hood upgrading some boring engineery things and squashing pesky bugs to make your Sing! experience better in lots of little ways like the app s load time! We re really proud of that one.

Oh boy oh boy it s the March Sing! update. Let s get right to it! New audio FX Double You ! The Double You is a doubler effect it s you x 2 for extra oomph and a fuller body sound. The pitch arrow on the singing screen went through a much needed tune up in order to be more responsive to your singing. Yep you ll see higher scores than before that s a good thing you re just that good. : The mic gain slider now shows the gain value to better help control the loudness or softness of your vocals. Remember though the gain slider is all relative to how loud or soft your vocals are when you re recording. We ve heard you! You can now clear the cache from the Settings menu and not have to delete and reinstall the app to clear up the phone memory. Show the estimated download time to help detect slow networks. A few housecleaning fixes under the hood. We love hearing from you! Stay in touch with the latest news songs released and updates on http: www.facebook.com Smule and send any questions or feedback to support smule.com.

3.0.3 Update Fixed a crash that was happening while you were listening. : Fixed location update issue where singers were appearing off the coast of Africa unless you re really singing in the middle of the ocean. 3.0.2 Update Hello happy shiny Sing!ers a bunch of things under the hood was fixed in this update. Crackling audio on the iPhone 5S is fixed. The iPhone 5S is so freaking fast we had to fix the underlying audio architecture to handle the speed. Thanks Maria66 for pointing it out initially. Sharing on the iPhone 5S is fixed. Sorry about missing this bug but you can now get back to sharing all your singing goodness. : Support for iPad landscape view during singing. Finally! We are continuing to work on more landscape optimizations for the next update. Thanks for being patient. More stability cleanup fixes all around. Excited about the iPad Air We are! Check out the landscape singing screen on the iPad Air for visual FX to match your selected audio FX. It needs the beefy new processors in order to be able to do the real time visual and audio FX at the same time. Visualizing voice is always tricky so we think this is a fun addition. Let us know what you think as we definitely want to work on making it even better. As always new songs are added every week! Suggest new songs to be added at http: bit.ly SuggestSongsForSmule We won t stop continuing to constantly work and improve Sing! for you so don t stop giving us feedback! Please let us know any feedback at support smule.com and like us on Facebook at http: www.facebook.com Smule for the latest updates news and feedback.

TOTAL iOS 7 DESIGN UPDATE! We re loving the new iOS 7 look and feel and we ve incorporated some of our favorite parts into the new design. This update also includes some major audio enhancements for your singing enjoyment. Some other major changes include: New sidebar navigation: all of your essentials including profile feed invites browsing are just one click away! Better browsing: new categories to help you discover even more artists. New vocal FX that take advantage of the processing power of the iPhone 5s: sing in a shower opera hall the Taj Mahal and more! New vocal wave: watch your voice dance as you sing your favorite songs! And much much more.
